modelIdentification.name: NETN-BASE
modelIdentification.description: Base module for NETN FOM modules. Mainly datatypes for use in other NETN FOM modules
modelIdentification.useHistory: v1.0.2 - Initial version developed by MSG-106 and MSG-134. Release included in NETN-FOM v2.0
v2.0.0 - Updated version developed by MSG-163. Release included in NETN-FOM v3.0

simpleData.name: EpochTimeSecInt64
simpleData.semantics: The number of seconds since 1 Jan 1970 (wallclock time) or since the start of the simulation (logical time).

simpleData.name: DirectionDegreesFloat32
simpleData.semantics: Compass direction measured clockwise relative to true north. Calculate values outside the range [0, 360) as modulo 360.

simpleData.name: LatLongDegreesFloat64
simpleData.semantics: Represents a measure of either latitude or longitude in decimal degrees of arc.

simpleData.name: MassDensityFloat32
simpleData.semantics: Density of substance measured as kg per cubic meter.

simpleData.name: TimeSecInt32
simpleData.semantics: A generic time interval in seconds.

simpleData.name: AltitudeMeterFloat64
simpleData.semantics: Generic representation of altitude defined by the context of use, i.e. height Above Mean Sea Level, height Above Ground Level.

simpleData.name: MassConcentrationFloat32
simpleData.semantics: Concentration of a substance measured as kg/m3.

enumeratedData.name: ActiveStatusEnum8
enumeratedData.semantics: A state which indicates the status of an object concerning its participation in the simulation. An object in an inactive state is not simulated and does not interact with other objects.

enumeratedData.name: AggregateMissionEnum16
enumeratedData.semantics: Representation of the general class or nature of activity related to a unit's mission. Enumerations are based on JC3IEDM action-event-category-code.

enumeratedData.name: DamageStatusEnhancedEnum32
enumeratedData.semantics: The damage status of an object.

enumeratedData.name: CancellationReasonEnum32
enumeratedData.semantics: Describes the reason for a cancellation.

enumeratedData.name: PointTypeEnum32
enumeratedData.semantics: Specifies if a point is defined by a location or by reference to a point object in the federation.

enumeratedData.name: PathTypeEnum32
enumeratedData.semantics: Specifies if a path is defined by waypoints or by reference to a path object in the federation.

enumeratedData.name: GeoLocationTypeEnum32
enumeratedData.semantics: Specifies different ways to reference geographical locations.

enumeratedData.name: AltitudeTypeEnum8
enumeratedData.semantics: The reference for altitude. AMSL = Above Mean Sea Level or AGL = Above Ground Level.

enumeratedData.name: EchelonEnum32
enumeratedData.semantics: The echelon level of a unit.

arrayData.name: Callsign
arrayData.semantics: Identifier for a simulated entity. Callsigns should be unique in the context in which they are used but are not required to be globally unique.

arrayData.name: TransactionId
arrayData.semantics: Unique identifier for a transaction. Encoded according to RFC 4122, section 4.1.2 using 16 bytes. Also referred to as Variant 1 or RFC 4122/DCE 1.1 UUIDs.

arrayData.name: UuidArrayOfHLAbyte16
arrayData.semantics:
Deprecated.
UUIDs are exchanged as a byte array and are encoded according to RFC
4122, section 4.1.2 using 16 bytes. Also referred to as Variant 1 or RFC 4122/DCE 1.1 UUIDs.
For example, 00112233-4455-8877-6699-aabbccddeeff is encoded as the bytes 00 11 22 33 44 55 88 77 66 99 aa bb cc dd ee ff.

arrayData.name: ArrayOfUuid
arrayData.semantics: Deprecated. Array of Unique Identifiers expressed as UUIDs.

arrayData.name: FederateName
arrayData.semantics: The unique name of a federate participating in an HLA federation.

arrayData.name: GeodeticPath
arrayData.semantics: A sequence of geodetic locations defining a path where each segment is a great circle between locations.

arrayData.name: GeodeticPolygon
arrayData.semantics: A sequence of geodetic locations defining a geographical area bounded by a closed path where the first and last locations in the sequence are connected. Each point is a geodetic coordinate in WGS84 on the earth surface, and each segment is a great circle between locations.

arrayData.name: ArrayOfWorldLocationStruct
arrayData.semantics: A polygonal chain (path) expressed as a sequence of geocentric points.

arrayData.name: ArrayOfStringType
arrayData.semantics: A generic representation of a set of strings.

arrayData.name: UUID
arrayData.semantics:
4122, section 4.1.2 using 16 bytes. Also referred to as Variant 1 or RFC 4122/DCE 1.1 UUIDs.
For example, 00112233-4455-8877-6699-aabbccddeeff is encoded as the bytes 00 11 22 33 44 55 88 77 66 99 aa bb cc dd ee ff.

arrayData.name: ArrayOfText64
arrayData.semantics: A set of names of max length 64 unicode characters.

arrayData.name: SymbolIdentifier
arrayData.semantics: A symbol identifier is represented as a string. The symbol standard used is indicated using an URI notation (uri:xxxxxxxxxx). The following uri should be used for common symbology standards app6b, app6b, app6c, app6c, 2525b, 2525c, 2525d. If not provided the symbol standard used is undefined.

fixedRecordData.name: NETN_SupplyStruct
fixedRecordData.semantics: Description of supply. Same encoding as RPR2 SupplyStruct.

field.name: SupplyType
field.semantics: The type of supply (as described in the Bit Encoded Values for Use with Protocols for Distributed Interactive Simulation Applications)

field.name: Quantity
field.semantics: The number of units of the supply type. The unit measure depends on the supply type and shall use the SI units of measurement used for such supplies.

fixedRecordData.name: GeodeticCircle
fixedRecordData.semantics: A geodetic point and radius specifying a circle on the surface of the earth WGS84 where the radius is a great circle distance on the surface.

field.name: CenterPoint
field.semantics: The center of the circular area. Lat, Long on WGS84.

field.name: Radius
field.semantics: The radius of the circular area.

fixedRecordData.name: GeodeticLocation
fixedRecordData.semantics: A geodetic point, specified by latitude and longitude, with unspecified altitude. WGS84

fixedRecordData.name: GeodeticQuadrangle
fixedRecordData.semantics: A latitude-longitude quadrangle is a region bounded by two meridians and two parallels.

fixedRecordData.name: GeodeticPoint
fixedRecordData.semantics: A geodetic point, specified by latitude, longitude and altitude.

variantRecordData.name: AreaVariantStruct

alternative.name: GeodeticPolygon
alternative.semantics: A sequence of geodetic locations defining a geographical area bounded by a closed path where the first and last locations in the sequence are connected. Each point is a geodetic coordinate in WGS84 on the earth surface, and each segment is a great circle between locations.

alternative.name: GeodeticCircle
alternative.semantics: A geodetic point and radius specifying a circle on the surface of the earth WGS84 where the radius is a great circle distance on the surface.

alternative.name: GeodeticQuadrangle
alternative.semantics: A latitude-longitude quadrangle is a region bounded by two meridians and two parallels.

variantRecordData.semantics: Description of an area relative to the earth's surface.

variantRecordData.name: PathVariantStruct

alternative.name: Waypoints
alternative.semantics:
The path defined by waypoints, not necessarily registered in the federation execution as a NETN_GeoObject.Path.
The array can be empty (size=0).

alternative.name: UUID
alternative.semantics: A UUID that referes to a NETN_GeoObject.Path that is registred iin the federation execution.

variantRecordData.semantics: Defines a path, either as a polygonal chain of waypoints or a UUID that refers to a path object in the federation.

variantRecordData.name: PointVariantStruct

alternative.name: UUID
alternative.semantics: A UUID that refers to a NETN_GeoObject.Point.

variantRecordData.semantics: Defines the point, either a Location or a UUID reference to a point object in the federation.
